  // Make calculate_priority static and pass last_evict as a parameter for better testability and clarity.
  static double calculate_priority(double pri_last_evict, uint64_t freq, uint64_t size) {
    if (size == 0) {
      return pri_last_evict + static_cast<double>(freq) * 1.0e6;
    }
    // Add a small logarithmic boost to frequency and a penalty for very large objects
    double freq_boost = static_cast<double>(freq) * (1.0 + 0.05 * std::log2(freq + 1));
    return pri_last_evict + freq_boost * 1.0e6 / (size + 1);
  }
